Current status:

```
cat npm-shrinkwrap.json \
| grep -vE '"(name|version|integrity|resolved|dependencies|requires|optional)"' \
| grep -v "lockfileVersion" \
| grep -v '[{}\^~*>|]' \
| grep -v '.x"' \
| awk '{$1=$1;print}' \
| sort \
| uniq \
| sed 's/"$/",/g'
```

This is gross, but I *think* I'll be able to pop this into `package.json` and it should install the same versions as it would if it understood the shrinkwrap file. Maybe?
